The paper deals with secret sharing schemes based on coding theory, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the concept of minimal linear codes, which is related to error-correcting codes (cs.CR) and cyclic codes (cs.CC). The paper also involves programming to obtain access structures of secret sharing schemes, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and security and privacy (cs.SI).
